The paper deals with pattern matching, which is a fundamental problem in computer science and is relevant to several sub-fields. The use of Hamming distance and the focus on time complexity suggest that the paper may belong to cs.DS (data structures and algorithms) or cs.DM (discrete mathematics). The mention of a conditional lower bound points towards cs.CC (computational complexity), while the use of matrix multiplication conjecture suggests cs.CG (computational geometry). Finally, the mention of smooth time trade-offs suggests cs.IT (information theory).
